      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0568P0-03076'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0568P0_19960123_GCR_61' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 11 [<span class="italic">Re-engagement for service</span>]:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0568P0-03077'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0568P0_19960123_GCR_62' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        [<span class="italic">Amendment No. 20 not moved</span>.]
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0568P0-03078'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0568P0_19960123_GCR_63' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Earl Howe</span> moved Amendment No. 21:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0568P0-03079'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0568P0_19960123_GCR_64' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <q>Page 4, line 27, leave out ("person") and insert ("man").</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0568P0-03080'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0568P0_19960123_GCR_65' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Earl said: In moving this amendment I shall speak also to Amendments Nos. 23 and 24, all of which address minor drafting points. The central issue in these amendments is that only men can enlist or re-engage, and the amendments make the drafting more precise. I beg to move.
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0568P0-03081'>
