      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0568P0-03144'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0568P0_19960123_GCR_129' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 16 [<span class="italic">Entitlement to discharge</span>]:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0568P0-03145'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0568P0_19960123_GCR_130' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        [<span class="italic">Amendment No. 40 not moved.</span>]
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0568P0-03146'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0568P0_19960123_GCR_131' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Earl Howe moved Amendment No. 41:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0568P0-03147'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0568P0_19960123_GCR_132' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <q>Page 7, line 5, leave out ("compulsory term of') and insert ("term of compulsory").</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0568P0-03148'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0568P0_19960123_GCR_133' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Earl said: In moving this amendment I shall speak also to Amendment No. 43. These are minor drafting amendments. Clause 16 specifies the conditions which entitle any man of any reserve force to be discharged. Amendments Nos. 41 and 43 ensure that the wording of Clause 16 is consistent with Clause 14. I beg to move.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0568P0-03149'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0568P0_19960123_GCR_134' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
